13
00:00:24,847 --> 00:00:26,694
What is the truth behind this?

14
00:00:26,694 --> 00:00:29,035
Is the demand of farmers right or wrong?

15
00:00:29,035 --> 00:00:31,662
Let's understand the reality of the farming industry

16
00:00:31,662 --> 00:00:33,252
in today's video.

17
00:00:40,961 --> 00:00:43,524
MRP, or Maximum Retail Price,

18
00:00:43,524 --> 00:00:47,019
is the maximum price at which 
things can be sold in the market.

19
00:00:47,019 --> 00:00:52,237
MRP exists to protect consumers 
and the general public in the country.

20
00:00:52,237 --> 00:00:55,061
So that no company or shopkeeper can exploit us.

21
00:00:55,061 --> 00:00:56,418
If there was no MRP,

22
00:00:56,418 --> 00:00:59,318
you can imagine how terribly 
people would have been exploited.

23
00:00:59,318 --> 00:01:01,632
If you were in the desert and facing water shortages,

24
00:01:01,632 --> 00:01:04,160
someone could try to sell a bottle of water for ₹2,000.

25
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:06,000
If there was a cooking oil shortage in your city,

26
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,625
you could be forced to buy cooking oil for ₹1,000 per litre.

27
00:01:08,625 --> 00:01:11,779
Now, in contrast to MRP, the opposite is MSP,

28
00:01:11,779 --> 00:01:13,459
that is, Minimum Support Price.

29
00:01:13,459 --> 00:01:17,326
The minimum amount that would be 
paid to the farmers for their crops.

30
00:01:17,636 --> 00:01:18,588
The reason remains the same.

31
00:01:18,588 --> 00:01:21,188
So that companies and middlemen can't exploit them.

32
00:01:21,188 --> 00:01:23,812
Even if the buyers set up a mafia,

33
00:01:23,812 --> 00:01:28,911
