50% profit will be added to that cost.

64
00:02:47,489 --> 00:02:50,557
And that will be the MSP they'll have to sell at."

65
00:02:50,557 --> 00:02:54,142
In India, MSP is issued by CACP,

66
00:02:54,142 --> 00:02:56,562
the Commission for Agriculture Costs and Prices.

67
00:02:56,562 --> 00:02:58,405
It is a decentralised agency

68
00:02:58,405 --> 00:03:00,702
which was established in 1965.

69
00:03:00,702 --> 00:03:05,078
And today, it functions under the Ministry 
of Agriculture and Farmers Welfare.

70
00:03:05,078 --> 00:03:08,480
But the question is, how should the MSP be decided?

71
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,039
How much should the MSP be?

72
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:12,131
In 2002, a committee was formed,

73
00:03:12,131 --> 00:03:14,655
the High Level Committee on Long Term Grain Policy,

74
00:03:14,655 --> 00:03:17,201
headed by economist Abhijit Sen.

75
00:03:17,201 --> 00:03:19,750
This committee said that MSP should be

76
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:22,151
based on C2 cost of production.

77
00:03:22,151 --> 00:03:24,050
But, what does this mean?

78
00:03:24,050 --> 00:03:27,666
To understand C2, we need to 
understand A2 and FL costs first.

79
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:29,328
First comes A2 cost.

80
00:03:29,328 --> 00:03:31,657
This is the cost that farmers have to pay

81
00:03:31,657 --> 00:03:33,458
as direct expenses.

82
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:42,289
Farmers buy seeds, fertilisers, pesticides, 
hire labourers to work in their fields, fuel cost,

83
00:03:42,289 --> 00:03:43,833
these are the A2 costs.

84
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:45,472
After this comes the FL cost.

85
00:03:45,472 --> 00:03:47,329
FL's full form is Family Labour.

86
00:03:47,329 --> 00:03:50,200
This cost is an estimated value

87
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,680
of unpaid family labour.

88
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,964
When a farmer works in his field,

89
00:03:53,964 --> 00:03:57,167
often his family members help him in farming.

90
00:03:57,167 --> 00:04:01,315
Because his family members invest their time to help him,

91
00:04:01,315 --> 00:04:03,286
there should be a labour cost for them too.

92
00:04:03,286 --> 00:04:06,831
They could have used this time to do some other job.

93
00:04:06,831 --> 00:04:09,324
They missed the opportunity of getting a job.

94
00:04:09,324 --> 00:04:12,337
This is known as Opportunity Cost in economics.

95
00:04:12,337 --> 00:04:14,061
So, these were the A2 and FL costs.

96
00:04:14,061 --> 00:04:19,665
Today, CACP takes A2 + FL cost to decide MSP

97
00:04:19,665 --> 00:04:21,574
and multiplies it by 1.5.

98
00:04:21,884 --> 00:04:24,543
This is how MSP is decided today.

99
00:04:24,543 --> 00:04:27,142
But Abhijit Sen's committee said that

100
00:04:27,142 --> 00:04:29,469
we need to consider the C2 cost.

101
00:04:29,469 --> 00:04:31,498
C2 refers to the Comprehensive Cost.

102
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,568
In C2 cost, not only do we take the A2 and FL costs,

103
00:04:34,568 --> 00:04:39,017
but we consider the cost of Owned Capital 
and the Rental Value of Land.

104
00:04:39,017 --> 00:04:41,127
You can understand this better with an example.

105
00:04:41,127 --> 00:04:44,005
Think of a photographer who has his own studio.

106
00:04:44,005 --> 00:04:45,428
To carry on his business,

107
00:04:45,428 --> 00:04:47,803
not only does he have to 
spend money to take photos,

108
00:04:47,803 --> 00:04:49,249
and to print photos,

109
00:04:49,249 --> 00:04:51,156
but also to buy a camera,

110
00:04:51,156 --> 00:04:53,046
and even to pay rent the rent for the studio.

111
00:04:53,046 --> 00:04:54,756
Like a photographer's studio,

112
00:04:54,756 --> 00:04:57,273
a farmer's land has a rental value.

113
00:04:57,686 --> 00:04:58,994
If the farmer owns the land,

114
00:04:58,994 --> 00:05:00,307
then it is his capital.

115
00:05:00,307 --> 00:05:01,876
And if he doesn't own it,

116
00:05:01,876 --> 00:05:03,439
then he pays rent on it.

117
00:05:03,439 --> 00:05:06,657
Apart from this, like the photographer's 
camera and studio lights,

118
00:05:06,657 --> 00:05:10,396
a farmer has to buy a tractor and a cultivator.

119
00:05:10,396 --> 00:05:13,824
The farmer doesn't buy a tractor just for fun.

120
00:05:13,824 --> 00:05:16,108
A tractor is bought to be used for agriculture.

121
00:05:16,108 --> 00:05:19,171
So, shouldn't that cost be taken into account too?

122
00:05:19,171 --> 00:05:22,580
All these are called Owned Capital Assets.

123
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:25,297
And Abhijeet Sen's commission report stated that

124
00:05:25,297 --> 00:05:31,016
in C2 cost, we should include 
the A2 cost, FL cost, and this extra cost.

125
00:05:31,016 --> 00:05:33,726
And then make it the new basis for MSP.

